      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This addition to the S. Philip Holt Papers, 1840-1938,
         consists of ninety-five items including correspondence, from
         1849 to 1877, of Joseph Miller, Lucilla Wood, and M. A.
         Harper; Loose leaf business papers, from 1840 to 1914, taken
         from Joseph Miller's account book; a small stamp collection,
         from 1914 to 1937; a tinted litho print of the Peale portrait
         of Thomas Jefferson; and an unidentified photograph of a small
         girl by the Holsinger Studio.</p>
      </scopecontent>
